# Multi-line Comments

When a comment spans more than one line, use a JSDoc-style `/** ... */` block instead
of multiple stacked `//` lines. Single-line comments stay as `//`.

- 2+ lines -> `/** ... */`, each inner line prefixed with ` * `.
- 1 line -> `//` is fine.
- Applies to explanatory/doc comments on functions, components, hooks, and constants.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — stacked single-line comments
// Self-updating toast body: shows a spinner while the tx is pending, then swaps
// to a success message with a block-explorer link once it confirms.
export const ToastTransaction = () => {
  /* ... */
};

// ✅ GOOD — one line stays //
// Force CLASSIC routing so we get a broadcastable transaction.

// ✅ GOOD — 2+ lines use a block
/**
 * Self-updating toast body: shows a spinner while the tx is pending, then swaps
 * to a success message with a block-explorer link once it confirms.
 */
export const ToastTransaction = () => {
  /* ... */
};
```
